<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="HB0371" sponsor="Tiara Auxier" designation="HB" otherSponsor="" otherHouse="Senate" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL0430" date="1/26/2026 10:01:623" printDate="01-26 10:01" subVer="0" minVer="0" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="code"><info><nextbuid>5</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="05/06/2026"><seclist><sect action="A" src="code" buid="1" uid="C53C-5-S101_2026050620260506" fromuid="C53C-5-S101_2025050720250507" sort="53C05 01010020260506" mtype="section" effdate="05/06/2026">53C-5-101</sect><sect action="A" src="code" buid="3" uid="C53C-5-S102_2026050620260506" fromuid="C53C-5-S102_1800010118000101" sort="53C05 01020020260506" mtype="section" effdate="05/06/2026">53C-5-102</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="4" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="05/06/2026"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">Grazing Permits Amendments</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: Tiara Auxier</sponsorhead><otherSponsorhead>Senate Sponsor: </otherSponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><gdhead lineno="4">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5">This bill addresses grazing on school and institutional trust lands.</gd><hphead lineno="6">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="7" slineno="0-7">This bill:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="8" slineno="0-8" level="1">requires the director of the School and Institutional Trust Lands Administration (SITLA) <ln numlevel="1" lineno="9" slineno="0-9"/>to prioritize multiple use and sustained yield in the management of school and <ln numlevel="1" lineno="10" slineno="0-10"/>institutional trust lands (trust lands);</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11" level="1">prohibits the director of SITLA from issuing permits for the non-use of trust lands if the <ln numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12"/>trust lands may be used for grazing; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="13" slineno="0-13" level="1">makes technical and conforming changes.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="15">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="16" slineno="0-16">Other Special Clauses:</oc><ocNone lineno="17">None</ocNone><sa numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="0-18">Utah Code Sections Affected:<saamd numlevel="1" lineno="19" slineno="0-19"><snhead>AMENDS:</snhead><sn num="53C-5-101" src="code" uid="C53C-5-S101_2026050620260506" buid="1" sort="53C05 01010020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="20" slineno="0-20"><bold>53C-5-101</bold>, as last amended by Laws of Utah 2025, Chapter 302</sn><sn num="53C-5-102" src="code" uid="C53C-5-S102_2026050620260506" buid="3" sort="53C05 01020020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="0-21"><bold>53C-5-102</bold>, as enacted by Laws of Utah 1994, Chapter 294</sn></saamd></sa></lt><enacthead lineno="22"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="0-23">Be it enacted by the Legislature of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="1" num="53C-5-101" type="amend" src="code" uid="C53C-5-S101_2026050620260506" sort="53C05 01010020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section number="53C-5-101" numlevel="1" lineno="25" slineno="1-2" type="amend"><secline lineno="24">Section 1. Section <bold>53C-5-101</bold> is amended to read:</secline><catline lineno="25"><bold>53C-5-101<parens/>. Management of range resources.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="1-null-1" dnum="1-o" numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="1-3" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display>(1)</display>The director is responsible for the efficient management of all range resources on lands <ln numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-4"/>under the director's administration, consistent with the director's fiduciary duties of <ln numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-5"/>financial support to the beneficiaries.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-3" dnum="_-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-6" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1001" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="12" groupid="8" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">The director shall:</amend><subsection ssid="1-4" dnum="_-o:a-i" numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-7" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1002" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="24" groupid="17" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">prioritize the principles of multiple use and sustained yield in the management of <ln numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="1-8"/>trust lands; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-6" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="1-9" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1003" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="29" groupid="21" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">base management of trust lands on sound resource management principles.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-2" dnum="2-o:_-i" numlevel="1" lineno="33" slineno="1-10" ea="erase" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="2" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1004" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="6" groupid="6" style="2" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" deltag="end">This management shall be based on sound resource management principles.</amend><amendoutend style="2"/></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="3" num="53C-5-102" type="amend" src="code" uid="C53C-5-S102_2026050620260506" sort="53C05 01020020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="34" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section number="53C-5-102" numlevel="1" lineno="35" slineno="2-2" type="amend"><secline lineno="34">Section 2. Section <bold>53C-5-102</bold> is amended to read:</secline><catline lineno="35"><bold>53C-5-102<parens/>. Grazing permits -- Treatment of permits on federal lands required <ln numlevel="1" lineno="36" slineno="2-3"/>by the state.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="3-null-1" dnum="1-o" numlevel="1" lineno="37" slineno="2-4" level="1" placement="noreturn" space="false"><display>(1)</display><subsection ssid="3-null-2" dnum="a-o" level="2" placement="sameline"><display>(a)</display>The director may issue grazing permits on trust lands under terms and conditions <ln numlevel="1" lineno="38" slineno="2-5"/>established by rules of the director.</subsection><subsection ssid="3-null-3" dnum="b-o" numlevel="1" lineno="39" slineno="2-6" level="2"><display>(b)</display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="11" groupid="10" style="2" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" deltag="both">Those terms shall be based</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="10" groupid="9" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">The director shall base the terms of a grazing permit</amend> on <ln numlevel="1" lineno="40" slineno="2-7"/>the fair market value of the <amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="9" groupid="8" style="2" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" deltag="both">permit</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="8" groupid="7" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">grazing use of the trust lands</amend>.</subsection><subsection ssid="3-7" dnum="_-o:c-i" numlevel="1" lineno="41" slineno="2-8" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1008" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(c)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="2" groupid="2" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">The director may not issue a permit for the non-use of trust lands if grazing is a <ln numlevel="1" lineno="42" slineno="2-9"/>viable use of the trust lands.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="3-null-4" dnum="2-o" numlevel="1" lineno="43" slineno="2-10" level="1" space="false"><display>(2)</display><subsection ssid="3-null-5" dnum="a-o" level="2" placement="sameline"><display>(a)</display>Upon selecting, exchanging, or otherwise acquiring lands of the United States, the <ln numlevel="1" lineno="44" slineno="2-11"/>director shall honor, for the remainder of the applicable term, all leases, permits, and <ln numlevel="1" lineno="45" slineno="2-12"/>contracts, and the related terms and conditions of user agreements on United States <ln numlevel="1" lineno="46" slineno="2-13"/>lands, including permitted stocking rates, grazing fee levels, access rights, and all <ln numlevel="1" lineno="47" slineno="2-14"/>existing activities that currently or historically have dictated an understanding of <ln numlevel="1" lineno="48" slineno="2-15"/>usage between the land user and the federal government.</subsection><subsection ssid="3-null-6" dnum="b-o" numlevel="1" lineno="49" slineno="2-16" level="2"><display>(b)</display>Improvements of the permittee or lessee to the land shall be honored by the state in <ln numlevel="1" lineno="50" slineno="2-17"/>the acquisition of federal lands.</subsection></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="4" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="true" numlevel="1" lineno="51" slineno="3-1" sn="3"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="51">Section 3.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="52"><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1" groupid="1" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="both">This bill takes effect on <effdate uid="code" date="5/6/2026">May 6, 2026</effdate>.</amend></sectionText></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>1-26-26 10:01 AM</tm></rev></foot></leg>